tasks.description:
Teammate request: The CARES dashboard currently uses a Kusto query against TuringBotTraceMDS to find exceptions (MimirServeIndexException) filtered by AgentQueryGateway|QmsSearchProvider|ScopedSearchContentProvider scopes. We should come up with some version of that query that shows us availability over time.

Original exception query (mangled version provided):

set query_results_cache_max_age = time(1h);
set truncationmaxsize=10048576000;
set maxmemoryconsumptionperiterator=68719476736;
set max_memory_consumption_per_query_per_node=68719476736;
set truncationmaxrecords=110000005;
set servertimeout=50m;
set query_timeout = 60m;
TuringBotTraceMDS
| where TIMESTAMP >= ago(2d)
| where CosmicPartition in ('sdf-master')
| where IsTestTraffic in ('0','1')
| where LogLevel in ("Error")
| where ScopeName matches regex "AgentQueryGateway|QmsSearchProvider|ScopedSearchContentProvider" and ScopeName !contains "Warmup"
| where Exception contains "MimirServeIndexException"
| extend ExceptionShort = substring(Exception, 0, 600)
| summarize Count = dcount(RequestId) by bin(TIMESTAMP, 30m)
| render timechart

Goal: Derive an availability metric from this — e.g. success rate, uptime percentage, or error-free intervals over time.
